The paper discusses the estimation of linear causal models from data, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper specifically focuses on non-gaussian distributions and the presence of confounding latent variables. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves statistical analysis and simulations, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
